 of these commissioners used the authority's extensive powers to rebuild Magdalen Bridge and reshape its approaches, abolish street markets, pull down old buildings, and pave, light and cleanse the streets. Some critics regretted these changes, others wanted more, but all could agree that, within thirty years, Oxford had been transformed.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aCity planningzEnglandzOxfordxHistoryy18th century. 0aPavementszEnglandzOxfordxHistoryy18th century. 4aBritish Local History. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Great Britain / General.2bisacsh  aCity of Oxford.  aGeorgian England.  aMagdalen Bridge.  aPaving Commission.  aUniversity of Oxford.  aarchitecture.  adrainage.  ahistory of civil engineering.  alocal government.  aroad building.  asewage systems.  astreet lighting.  atown and gown in Oxford.  atown planning.  atransport.  aturnpikes.  aurban improvement.1 aGraham, Malcolm, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311142849940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781805433132?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781805433132423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781805433132/original  a978-3-11-142849-9  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles